a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes a b :: complex
assumes h0 : "a = Complex (Re (-3)) (Im (-2))"
and h1 : "b = Complex (Re 1) (Im 4)"
shows  "a - b = Complex (Re (-4)) (Im (-6))"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Simplify $(-3-2i)-(1+4i)$. The final Answer is -4-6i
 ### Proof
 $(-3-2i)-(1+4i)= -3 -2i -1 - 4i= \boxed{-4-6i}$.
 *)

theorem
fixes a b :: complex
assumes h0 : "a = Complex (Re (-3)) (Im (-2))"
and h1 : "b = Complex (Re 1) (Im 4)"
shows  "a - b = Complex (Re (-4)) (Im (-6))"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
a_0.informal problem: Calculate the result of subtracting the complex number $(1 + 4i)$ from the complex number $(-3 - 2i)$. The final result is $(-4 - 6i)$.
